WEBVTT

00:00:14.830 --> 00:00:21.629
Jehovah cherishes all who serve him loyally, regardless of their circumstances.

00:00:21.629 --> 00:00:27.670
Do you truly understand why Jehovah loves those who situation in life may be very different

00:00:27.670 --> 00:00:29.949
from your own?

00:00:29.949 --> 00:00:38.100
If so, you are in a much better position to show them your love and support.

00:00:38.100 --> 00:00:43.740
Please listen closely as Brother William Mellonfont, a helper to the Teaching Committee, begins

00:00:43.740 --> 00:00:50.380
this symposium with the talk, successful fighters for the faith, those with unbelieving

00:00:50.380 --> 00:00:52.219
mates.

00:00:52.219 --> 00:00:55.659
Each speaker will then introduce the one to follow.

00:00:55.659 --> 00:01:05.260
Brother Mellonfont, you have our attention.

00:01:05.260 --> 00:01:15.459
Jehovah God's inspired word makes this significant declaration at Titus, chapter 2, and

00:01:15.459 --> 00:01:17.060
verse 11.

00:01:17.060 --> 00:01:19.019
It reads,

00:01:19.019 --> 00:01:27.819
For the undeserved kindness of God has been manifested, bringing salvation to all sorts

00:01:27.819 --> 00:01:29.140
of people.

00:01:29.140 --> 00:01:33.700
Yes, to all sorts of people.

00:01:33.700 --> 00:01:40.140
This was true in the first century, and it's true today more than ever before.

00:01:40.140 --> 00:01:46.260
We are a worldwide brotherhood made up of all sorts of people who have come to a knowledge

00:01:46.260 --> 00:01:52.900
of the truth, and we have made the decision to serve Jehovah.

00:01:52.900 --> 00:01:57.780
In this symposium, we will discuss three sorts of people.

00:01:57.780 --> 00:02:07.500
First, those whose mates are not yet Jehovah's Witnesses, second, those who are being raised

00:02:07.500 --> 00:02:16.139
by one believing parent or relative, and third, those who are single.

00:02:16.139 --> 00:02:21.860
Many brothers and sisters who find themselves in these situations are successfully putting

00:02:21.860 --> 00:02:28.300
up a hard fight for the faith as stated in Jude, verse 3.

00:02:28.300 --> 00:02:33.539
And all of them are valuable assets to the congregation.

00:02:33.539 --> 00:02:41.460
So as we discuss each situation during this symposium, please focus your attention on those

00:02:41.460 --> 00:02:47.900
who are in the congregation that you attend and ask yourself.

00:02:47.900 --> 00:02:55.580
How can I show my appreciation for brothers and sisters who have these circumstances?

00:02:55.580 --> 00:03:04.580
And ask yourself, if I am in one of the situations being discussed, what will help me to continue

00:03:04.580 --> 00:03:09.800
to fight successfully for the faith?

00:03:09.800 --> 00:03:16.159
This talk will focus on Christians with unbelieving mates.

00:03:16.159 --> 00:03:22.280
For a well-known example, we look back to the first century to a woman named Eunice, the

00:03:22.280 --> 00:03:24.599
mother of Timothy.

00:03:24.599 --> 00:03:31.879
She is referred to in Acts 161, which says that Timothy was the son of a believing Jewish

00:03:31.879 --> 00:03:35.919
woman, but of a Greek father.

00:03:35.919 --> 00:03:42.199
So it refers to Eunice as a believing woman, but it does not refer to Timothy's father

00:03:42.199 --> 00:03:44.520
as a believing man.

00:03:44.520 --> 00:03:49.680
The point is that Timothy's father was not a Christian.

00:03:49.680 --> 00:03:55.900
Nevertheless, Eunice, his mother, along with Lois, his grandmother, taught Timothy the

00:03:55.900 --> 00:04:03.199
holy writings, the truth as found in God's Word.

00:04:03.199 --> 00:04:12.080
When we speak of unbelieving mates, we recognize that their circumstances are not all the same.

00:04:12.080 --> 00:04:16.519
Some non-witness mates oppose true worship.

00:04:16.519 --> 00:04:24.639
Others are indifferent, and others may be tolerant, even somewhat interested and supportive,

00:04:24.639 --> 00:04:29.720
but they may not be progressing toward baptism.

00:04:29.720 --> 00:04:36.160
Some mates of believers are baptized, but they have weakened spiritually.

00:04:36.160 --> 00:04:44.120
They may no longer be regular at meetings, go in service, or participate in family worship.

00:04:44.120 --> 00:04:52.639
And last of all, sad to say, some mates are disfellowshipped, but we never give up on

00:04:52.639 --> 00:04:59.480
unbelieving mates, and we always hope that any who are disfellowshipped will come to

00:04:59.480 --> 00:05:06.360
their senses, repent, and return to Jehovah.

00:05:06.360 --> 00:05:12.000
Is there something that we as publishers in the congregation can do to show appreciation

00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:16.879
for fellow believers whose mates are not yet serving Jehovah?

00:05:16.879 --> 00:05:19.800
Yes, there is.

00:05:19.800 --> 00:05:27.680
And the Apostle Paul tells us at Philippians chapter 3, verse 17, that we can learn from

00:05:27.680 --> 00:05:31.519
their good example and imitate them.

00:05:31.560 --> 00:05:36.279
Philippians chapter 3, verse 17 says,

00:05:36.279 --> 00:05:44.759
"...unitedly become imitators of me, brothers, and keep your eye on those who are walking

00:05:44.759 --> 00:05:50.920
in a way that is in harmony with the example we set for you."

00:05:50.920 --> 00:05:59.839
So Paul tells us to look closely at his example and the fine example of others in the congregation.

00:05:59.839 --> 00:06:06.920
Among those setting a fine example are brothers and sisters who have unbelieving mates.

00:06:06.920 --> 00:06:11.759
They have worked hard to maintain a strong relationship with Jehovah.

00:06:11.759 --> 00:06:17.720
They have cultivated self-discipline to keep a good schedule of theocratic activities.

00:06:17.720 --> 00:06:25.720
And many have become proficient in balancing family obligations with spiritual pursuits.

00:06:25.720 --> 00:06:31.160
It's not easy, but they are doing it.

00:06:31.160 --> 00:06:36.399
So how should we view them and treat them?

00:06:36.399 --> 00:06:41.199
We do what Philippians chapter 2, verse 4 tells us to do.

00:06:41.199 --> 00:06:48.920
We look out not only for our own interests, but also for the interests of others.

00:06:48.920 --> 00:06:53.160
That means that we show concern for their well-being.

00:06:53.160 --> 00:06:56.079
We treat them with respect.

00:06:56.079 --> 00:06:58.639
We certainly do not ignore them.

00:06:58.639 --> 00:07:05.040
We recognize that as spiritual people, they have much to offer.

00:07:05.040 --> 00:07:12.839
Isn't it wonderful that we are family and we belong to one another?

00:07:12.839 --> 00:07:17.720
We take brothers and sisters who have unbelieving mates into account.

00:07:17.720 --> 00:07:24.120
And we look out for their interests as the scripture states because we love them and

00:07:24.120 --> 00:07:27.160
we see their good qualities.

00:07:27.160 --> 00:07:31.600
So what can we do?

00:07:31.600 --> 00:07:37.240
Whenever possible, we should include them in our activities.

00:07:37.240 --> 00:07:40.680
But what else can we do?

00:07:40.680 --> 00:07:47.040
We can show interest in their mates and try to help them spiritually.

00:07:47.040 --> 00:07:56.000
For example, if circumstances allow, invite them with their mates for a meal or to a gathering.

00:07:56.000 --> 00:08:01.600
You know that friendliness and upbuilding conversation can have a powerful effect on a person's

00:08:01.600 --> 00:08:03.680
heart.

00:08:03.680 --> 00:08:11.199
As you watch the following video, think about how you can show appreciation for any in your

00:08:11.199 --> 00:08:18.399
congregation whose mates are not presently serving Jehovah.

00:08:18.399 --> 00:08:23.079
It was when my husband was really opposed.

00:08:23.079 --> 00:08:33.039
One night, he put a knife to his stomach and said, will you choose me or the truth?

00:08:33.039 --> 00:08:36.240
My husband was cooperative.

00:08:36.240 --> 00:08:40.759
He would wave goodbyes we went to the meetings.

00:08:40.759 --> 00:08:45.320
But he wasn't interested at all.

00:08:45.320 --> 00:08:53.009
I felt really jealous when I saw families sitting together at assemblies.

00:08:53.009 --> 00:09:00.610
Because of work and taking care of his mother, my husband gradually started missing meetings.

00:09:00.610 --> 00:09:05.850
