01:00:26.619 --> 01:00:31.119
We could kind of think of meditation like a bridge.

01:00:31.119 --> 01:00:33.820
On this side of the river, we have knowing

01:00:33.820 --> 01:00:35.420
what is the right thing to do.

01:00:35.420 --> 01:00:39.219
And on this side, we have actually doing it.

01:00:39.219 --> 01:00:43.019
Meditation is the bridge that closes the gap

01:00:43.019 --> 01:00:45.920
between knowing and doing.

01:00:45.920 --> 01:00:48.019
And if we find ourselves always kind of knowing

01:00:48.019 --> 01:00:51.619
what the right thing is to do, but not actually doing it,

01:00:51.619 --> 01:00:55.920
meditation is the bridge to help us close that gap

01:00:55.920 --> 01:01:00.230
between knowing and doing.

01:01:00.230 --> 01:01:03.329
Well, how can you meditate on God's Word?

01:01:03.329 --> 01:01:06.429
Well, after reading a portion of the Bible

01:01:06.429 --> 01:01:09.130
or one of our publications,

01:01:09.130 --> 01:01:13.530
take a few moments to think deeply about what you have read.

01:01:13.530 --> 01:01:15.429
Ask yourself,

01:01:15.429 --> 01:01:21.079
what do I learn about Jehovah when I read this account?

01:01:21.079 --> 01:01:25.579
How does this account make me feel about Jehovah?

01:01:25.579 --> 01:01:28.179
How can I apply this in my life?

01:01:28.179 --> 01:01:33.429
Or how can I use this to help others?

01:01:33.429 --> 01:01:36.329
So let's review our first question.

01:01:36.329 --> 01:01:40.530
How can you feed the fire of your faith?

01:01:40.530 --> 01:01:46.230
Read and meditate on God's Word each day.

01:01:46.230 --> 01:01:48.829
Let's look at our second question.

01:01:48.829 --> 01:01:53.230
What does it mean to exercise faith?

01:01:53.230 --> 01:01:56.130
Well, Jesus told us that more was required

01:01:56.130 --> 01:01:58.530
than just believing in Him.

01:01:58.530 --> 01:02:01.329
Let's read John chapter 3 and verse 16

01:02:01.329 --> 01:02:07.699
to see the emphasis that Jesus put on exercising faith.

01:02:07.699 --> 01:02:11.199
John chapter 3 and verse 16.

01:02:11.199 --> 01:02:13.500
For God loved the world so much

01:02:13.500 --> 01:02:16.099
that He gave His only begotten Son

01:02:16.099 --> 01:02:20.300
so that everyone exercising faith in Him

01:02:20.300 --> 01:02:26.699
might not be destroyed but have ever lasting life.

01:02:26.699 --> 01:02:31.800
So what then does it mean to exercise faith?

01:02:31.800 --> 01:02:35.099
A study note on this verse explains

01:02:35.099 --> 01:02:38.099
to exercise faith includes the idea

01:02:38.099 --> 01:02:41.599
of demonstrating one's strong beliefs or faith

01:02:41.599 --> 01:02:45.099
by obeying God.

01:02:45.099 --> 01:02:47.400
Now Abraham was a powerful example

01:02:47.400 --> 01:02:50.900
of proving his faith by obedience.

01:02:50.900 --> 01:02:54.699
Let's look at a very wonderful description

01:02:54.699 --> 01:02:58.699
of Abraham's faith in James chapter 2

01:02:58.699 --> 01:03:03.139
and verses 21 through 23.

01:03:03.139 --> 01:03:08.179
James chapter 2 verses 21 through 23.

01:03:08.179 --> 01:03:11.980
Was not Abraham our father declared righteous by works

01:03:11.980 --> 01:03:15.679
after he offered up Isaac his son on the altar?

01:03:15.679 --> 01:03:19.980
You see that his faith was active along with his works

01:03:19.980 --> 01:03:24.079
and his faith was perfected by his works.

01:03:24.079 --> 01:03:27.079
And the scripture was fulfilled that says

01:03:27.079 --> 01:03:30.380
Abraham put faith in Jehovah

01:03:30.380 --> 01:03:33.980
and it was counted to him as righteousness

01:03:33.980 --> 01:03:40.320
and he came to be called Jehovah's Friend.

01:03:40.320 --> 01:03:45.219
One way read and we meditate on the account of Abraham

01:03:45.219 --> 01:03:48.619
we can feel the emotions that he must have felt

01:03:48.619 --> 01:03:52.219
and being asked to offer up his son Isaac,

01:03:52.219 --> 01:03:56.019
the only son that he and Sarah had.

01:03:56.019 --> 01:03:59.820
How could Abraham make such a very difficult decision?

01:03:59.820 --> 01:04:01.219
Well long before this,

01:04:01.219 --> 01:04:02.820
Abraham had made a decision

01:04:02.820 --> 01:04:04.519
that he would obey Jehovah

01:04:04.519 --> 01:04:07.320
and serve him in everything.

01:04:07.320 --> 01:04:09.619
And that decision years before

01:04:09.619 --> 01:04:11.619
to obey Jehovah and all things

01:04:11.619 --> 01:04:14.420
helped Abraham to make all the other decisions

01:04:14.420 --> 01:04:16.719
in life clear what he should do.

01:04:16.719 --> 01:04:18.920
He did not always have to consider

01:04:18.920 --> 01:04:22.719
should I do what Jehovah asks or not?

01:04:22.719 --> 01:04:27.519
As difficult a request as it was to offer up his son

01:04:27.519 --> 01:04:29.420
Abraham did not delay

01:04:29.420 --> 01:04:36.059
and took action immediately to obey Jehovah's request.

01:04:36.059 --> 01:04:37.860
Now by your baptism today

01:04:37.860 --> 01:04:39.559
you're telling everyone

01:04:39.559 --> 01:04:44.059
that you have dedicated your life to Jehovah

01:04:44.159 --> 01:04:46.159
to serve and obey him

01:04:46.159 --> 01:04:49.159
for the rest of your life.

01:04:49.159 --> 01:04:52.460
Now let's consider three scriptures

01:04:52.460 --> 01:04:55.659
and see how you can show your faith

01:04:55.659 --> 01:04:58.260
by your actions.

01:04:58.260 --> 01:04:59.960
Once we read each scripture

01:04:59.960 --> 01:05:02.360
we'll consider each scripture is part

01:05:02.360 --> 01:05:04.260
of your dedication promise

01:05:04.260 --> 01:05:08.260
and how you can show your faith in action.

01:05:08.260 --> 01:05:14.710
Our first scripture is Hebrews chapter 10 and verse 25.

01:05:14.710 --> 01:05:21.760
Hebrews chapter 10 and verse 25.

01:05:21.760 --> 01:05:24.159
Not forsaking our meetings together

01:05:24.159 --> 01:05:26.059
as some have the custom,

01:05:26.059 --> 01:05:28.059
but encouraging one another

01:05:28.059 --> 01:05:34.239
and all the more so as you see the day drawing near.

01:05:34.239 --> 01:05:36.239
Your dedication promise

01:05:36.239 --> 01:05:40.940
I will attend all meetings, assemblies and conventions.

01:05:40.940 --> 01:05:43.940
Well how do you show that by faith in action?

01:05:43.940 --> 01:05:45.940
Well you really need a job

01:05:45.940 --> 01:05:48.039
but you say no to a job

01:05:48.039 --> 01:05:52.039
that would mean that you would regularly miss meetings.

01:05:52.039 --> 01:05:53.539
You don't have to decide

01:05:53.539 --> 01:05:55.739
should I go to meetings or not?

01:05:55.739 --> 01:05:58.039
You've already made that decision

01:05:58.039 --> 01:06:01.039
when you dedicated yourself to Jehovah.

01:06:02.239 --> 01:06:03.539
Our second scripture

01:06:03.539 --> 01:06:09.340
Romans chapter 10 and verse 10.

01:06:09.340 --> 01:06:14.989
Romans chapter 10 and verse 10.

01:06:14.989 --> 01:06:19.489
For with the heart one exercises faith for righteousness

01:06:19.489 --> 01:06:21.190
but with the mouth

01:06:21.190 --> 01:06:25.690
one makes public declaration for salvation.

01:06:25.690 --> 01:06:27.789
So your dedication promise

01:06:27.789 --> 01:06:31.489
I want everyone to know about Jehovah.

01:06:31.489 --> 01:06:33.590
Your faith in action?

01:06:33.590 --> 01:06:34.889
Well going to bed early

01:06:34.889 --> 01:06:38.590
so that you can get up for field service the next morning.

01:06:38.590 --> 01:06:41.889
Auxiliary pioneering when you can.

01:06:41.889 --> 01:06:44.289
You schedule field service first

01:06:44.289 --> 01:06:47.989
and then other activities later in the day

01:06:47.989 --> 01:06:50.389
or adapting to different forms of the ministry

01:06:50.389 --> 01:06:55.239
like telephone witnessing or letter writing.

01:06:55.239 --> 01:06:56.840
Our third scripture

01:06:56.840 --> 01:07:03.000
Mark chapter 11 and verse 24.

01:07:03.000 --> 01:07:12.750
Mark chapter 11 and verse 24.

01:07:12.750 --> 01:07:14.449
This is why I tell you

01:07:14.449 --> 01:07:17.449
all the things you pray and ask for

01:07:17.449 --> 01:07:20.449
have faith that you have received them

01:07:20.449 --> 01:07:23.949
and you will have them.

01:07:23.949 --> 01:07:25.550
Well your dedication promise

01:07:25.550 --> 01:07:29.650
I will constantly seek Jehovah's direction in prayer.

01:07:29.650 --> 01:07:31.849
Your faith in action

01:07:31.849 --> 01:07:35.449
when you're tempted to play a violent video game

01:07:35.449 --> 01:07:39.349
you reject that game and play something else.

01:07:39.349 --> 01:07:41.449
When faced with a serious illness

01:07:41.449 --> 01:07:43.550
you pray for calm and wisdom

01:07:43.550 --> 01:07:46.349
to make good decisions.

01:07:46.349 --> 01:07:49.150
When you feel yourself getting angry with someone

01:07:49.150 --> 01:07:53.550
you pray for self control.

01:07:53.550 --> 01:07:56.050
Now we could use many more scriptures

01:07:56.050 --> 01:07:58.250
and we could give you many more examples

01:07:58.349 --> 01:08:00.150
of how you can exercise

01:08:00.150 --> 01:08:03.349
and show your faith by your actions.

01:08:03.349 --> 01:08:04.949
The point is

01:08:04.949 --> 01:08:06.550
that you baptismal candidates

01:08:06.550 --> 01:08:08.349
have dedicated your life

01:08:08.349 --> 01:08:11.750
to Jehovah and to do his will.

01:08:11.750 --> 01:08:15.150
This one decision to dedicate your life

01:08:15.150 --> 01:08:17.850
and to live by his standards

01:08:17.850 --> 01:08:21.149
sets the spiritual and moral foundation

01:08:21.149 --> 01:08:23.149
for all the decisions you will make

01:08:23.149 --> 01:08:26.489
from this day forward.

01:08:26.489 --> 01:08:29.090
So let's review our second question

01:08:29.090 --> 01:08:32.689
what does it mean to exercise faith?

01:08:32.689 --> 01:08:39.250
We show our faith by our obedience to God.

01:08:39.250 --> 01:08:43.210
Now let's go to our third question

01:08:43.210 --> 01:08:48.199
how will Jehovah reward your faith?

01:08:48.199 --> 01:08:51.000
Jehovah loves his faithful worshipers

01:08:51.000 --> 01:08:52.699
he wants the best for us

01:08:52.699 --> 01:08:56.199
and he wants us to be happy.

01:08:56.199 --> 01:08:58.699
Jehovah sees every time you do something

01:08:58.699 --> 01:09:00.199
to demonstrate your faith

01:09:00.199 --> 01:09:01.500
to show faith in action

01:09:01.500 --> 01:09:04.600
to be obedient to him.

01:09:04.600 --> 01:09:08.100
Now some feel that God or Jehovah

01:09:08.100 --> 01:09:11.199
is always watching out for the bad things they do.

01:09:11.199 --> 01:09:13.100
Maybe keeping a ledger track

01:09:13.100 --> 01:09:16.800
of all these things bad that a person does.

01:09:16.800 --> 01:09:18.399
But Jehovah is not doing that.

01:09:18.399 --> 01:09:20.100
He's actually looking for the good

01:09:20.100 --> 01:09:23.800
and rejoicing in the good that we are doing.

01:09:23.800 --> 01:09:25.199
We could kind of illustrate it

01:09:25.199 --> 01:09:26.899
the way that many of us

01:09:26.899 --> 01:09:29.100
are taking so many pictures these days.

01:09:29.100 --> 01:09:31.699
We all have phones, cameras.

01:09:31.699 --> 01:09:33.399
We're taking lots of pictures.

01:09:33.399 --> 01:09:35.399
And maybe you've noticed that at one point

01:09:35.399 --> 01:09:37.800
you take a picture of one of your friends

01:09:37.800 --> 01:09:40.100
and they have kind of a funny look on their face

01:09:40.100 --> 01:09:43.699
or they are in the middle of eating something.

01:09:43.699 --> 01:09:46.199
If you show your friend that picture

01:09:46.199 --> 01:09:47.899
what do they often say?

01:09:47.899 --> 01:09:50.100
Could you please delete that?

01:09:50.100 --> 01:09:53.199
That's not the picture they want you to show

01:09:53.199 --> 01:09:54.199
to other people.

01:09:54.199 --> 01:09:56.899
And that's not the picture you want to show of them.

01:09:56.899 --> 01:09:58.800
Now I want you to imagine for a moment

01:09:58.800 --> 01:10:04.199
that Jehovah has a digital photo album of you.

01:10:04.199 --> 01:10:08.000
Which pictures do you think he's keeping there?

01:10:08.000 --> 01:10:10.600
The ones where we made serious mistakes?

01:10:10.600 --> 01:10:14.100
The ones where we did something dumb?

01:10:14.100 --> 01:10:17.300
No, based on your repentance

01:10:17.300 --> 01:10:18.600
and the ransom sacrifice.

01:10:18.600 --> 01:10:19.699
Those are deleted.

01:10:19.699 --> 01:10:21.699
They're gone.

01:10:21.699 --> 01:10:24.300
He has in his photo album of you

01:10:24.300 --> 01:10:26.199
the beautiful pictures,

01:10:26.199 --> 01:10:28.399
the beautiful moments that he's proud of

01:10:28.399 --> 01:10:32.399
that you showed your faith in action.

01:10:32.399 --> 01:10:36.699
Jehovah wants to reward your faith.

01:10:36.699 --> 01:10:41.399
In Hebrews chapter 11 and verse 6

01:10:41.399 --> 01:10:44.600
we can see how Jehovah feels about his servants

01:10:44.600 --> 01:10:48.300
by what he says here about rewarding them.

01:10:48.300 --> 01:10:51.800
Hebrews chapter 11 and verse 6.

01:10:51.800 --> 01:10:53.699
Moreover, without faith

01:10:53.699 --> 01:10:57.000
it is impossible to please God well

01:10:57.100 --> 01:10:59.199
for whoever approaches God

01:10:59.199 --> 01:11:01.000
must believe that he is

01:11:01.000 --> 01:11:03.600
and that he becomes the rewarder

01:11:03.600 --> 01:11:08.510
of those earnestly seeking him.

01:11:08.510 --> 01:11:11.510
So when listing all these other examples of faith

01:11:11.510 --> 01:11:13.810
there in chapter 11 of Hebrews,

01:11:13.810 --> 01:11:16.510
the Apostle Paul pauses for a moment

01:11:16.510 --> 01:11:20.810
to remind us that Jehovah becomes the rewarder

01:11:20.810 --> 01:11:24.210
of those earnestly seeking him.

01:11:24.210 --> 01:11:27.010
Now when you take the time

01:11:27.010 --> 01:11:29.510
and effort to build a fire,

01:11:29.510 --> 01:11:32.609
what reward do you get in return?

01:11:32.609 --> 01:11:35.909
Well, you get the warmth and light of that fire.

01:11:35.909 --> 01:11:39.810
You can keep yourself and others warm by the fire.

01:11:39.810 --> 01:11:42.909
And a fire gives off a beautiful light

01:11:42.909 --> 01:11:46.409
that can be very welcome on a dark night.

01:11:46.409 --> 01:11:48.210
The sounds of a crackling fire

01:11:48.210 --> 01:11:52.689
can make us feel safe and happy.

01:11:52.689 --> 01:11:55.090
How will Jehovah reward

01:11:55.189 --> 01:11:56.689
his faithful worshippers

01:11:56.689 --> 01:11:59.189
for their fire of faith?

01:11:59.189 --> 01:12:01.090
Well, ultimately he will reward us

01:12:01.090 --> 01:12:03.489
with everlasting life.

01:12:03.489 --> 01:12:04.489
During his ministry,

01:12:04.489 --> 01:12:06.689
Jesus repeatedly promised

01:12:06.689 --> 01:12:07.989
that his faithful servants

01:12:07.989 --> 01:12:11.500
would get everlasting life.

01:12:11.500 --> 01:12:15.500
Just as Jehovah provided the rewards of a wood fire,

01:12:15.500 --> 01:12:17.500
he also provides many gifts

01:12:17.500 --> 01:12:19.300
that come when we build

01:12:19.300 --> 01:12:22.300
and feed our fire of faith.

01:12:22.300 --> 01:12:23.500
Consider some of the rewards

01:12:23.500 --> 01:12:25.699
that Jehovah gives us now.

01:12:25.800 --> 01:12:29.300
The reward of his word, the Bible,

01:12:29.300 --> 01:12:31.800
gives us the best advice for life.

01:12:31.800 --> 01:12:33.000
It lights our way

01:12:33.000 --> 01:12:37.100
in a spiritually dark world.

01:12:37.100 --> 01:12:38.600
The reward of the ministry

01:12:38.600 --> 01:12:42.699
the most satisfying work that we can do.

01:12:42.699 --> 01:12:45.899
The reward of Holy Spirit,

01:12:45.899 --> 01:12:49.000
a powerful helper in times of trials.

01:12:49.000 --> 01:12:53.600
Remember you are never alone.

01:12:53.600 --> 01:12:56.100
And the reward of our loving group

01:12:56.100 --> 01:12:58.399
of brothers and sisters around the world,

01:12:58.399 --> 01:13:03.470
a source of great warmth and comfort.

01:13:03.470 --> 01:13:04.569
In conclusion,

01:13:04.569 --> 01:13:07.569
let's review our three questions.

01:13:07.569 --> 01:13:12.369
One, how can you feed your fire of faith?

01:13:12.369 --> 01:13:17.069
Read and meditate on God's word each day.

01:13:17.069 --> 01:13:21.369
Two, what does it mean to exercise faith?

01:13:21.369 --> 01:13:26.680
We show our faith by our obedience to God.

01:13:26.680 --> 01:13:31.979
And three, how will Jehovah reward your faith?

01:13:31.979 --> 01:13:36.020
Everlasting life.

01:13:36.020 --> 01:13:38.119
Please take note of this day.

01:13:38.119 --> 01:13:39.020
Remember it.

01:13:39.020 --> 01:13:40.819
Write it down.

01:13:40.819 --> 01:13:44.020
Each time you hear baptism talk in the future,

01:13:44.020 --> 01:13:47.520
take that opportunity to reflect on your baptism

01:13:47.520 --> 01:13:50.020
and the many blessings that you have received

01:13:50.020 --> 01:13:52.520
because of the decision that you made

01:13:52.520 --> 01:13:56.819
to dedicate your life to Jehovah.

01:13:56.819 --> 01:14:00.819
Jehovah, want you to be happy and to enjoy life.

01:14:00.819 --> 01:14:03.720
All eight and a half million plus

01:14:03.720 --> 01:14:05.119
of your brothers and sisters

01:14:05.119 --> 01:14:06.920
that are watching this program

01:14:06.920 --> 01:14:09.520
are with you and heart and mind

01:14:09.520 --> 01:14:13.250
and we want you to be happy.

01:14:13.250 --> 01:14:14.949
Keep clear in mind, though,

01:14:14.949 --> 01:14:16.850
that happiness is not something

01:14:16.850 --> 01:14:19.050
that you can buy for yourself

01:14:19.050 --> 01:14:20.949
or get for yourself

01:14:20.949 --> 01:14:24.449
or you can't get it by loving yourself.

01:14:24.449 --> 01:14:26.550
Just like the warmth and light

01:14:26.550 --> 01:14:29.550
are byproducts of a wood fire,

01:14:29.550 --> 01:14:32.649
so to happiness is a byproduct

01:14:32.649 --> 01:14:34.750
of faith and love

01:14:34.750 --> 01:14:38.050
for others and for Jehovah.

01:14:38.050 --> 01:14:40.149
We could say that happiness

01:14:40.149 --> 01:14:45.819
is the warmth and glow from love's fire.

01:14:45.819 --> 01:14:47.619
The world will tell you

01:14:47.619 --> 01:14:49.220
you can follow your dreams.

01:14:49.220 --> 01:14:52.220
You can be anything you want to be.

01:14:52.220 --> 01:14:57.220
But it is far better to let Jehovah dream for you.

01:14:57.220 --> 01:14:59.619
Your life serving Jehovah

01:14:59.619 --> 01:15:02.619
can be far greater than anything

01:15:02.619 --> 01:15:05.619
you could dream up for yourself.

01:15:05.619 --> 01:15:08.020
Please, from this day forward,

01:15:08.020 --> 01:15:11.020
be determined to keep feeding

01:15:11.020 --> 01:15:15.529
and exercising your faith.

01:15:15.529 --> 01:15:18.329
Thank you, brother Ekran.

01:15:18.329 --> 01:15:19.829
Again, this year,

01:15:19.829 --> 01:15:21.529
the circumstances for baptism

01:15:21.529 --> 01:15:24.430
will vary in each location.

01:15:24.430 --> 01:15:25.930
Be assured that your elders

01:15:25.930 --> 01:15:27.729
have made suitable provisions

01:15:27.729 --> 01:15:29.930
in accord with local circumstances

01:15:29.930 --> 01:15:32.130
for candidates to be baptized

01:15:32.130 --> 01:15:35.229
after the conclusion of this session.

01:15:35.229 --> 01:15:39.529
And now, let's sing together song number 79,

01:15:39.529 --> 01:15:42.430
teach them to stand firm.

01:15:42.430 --> 01:15:44.130
After the song,

01:15:44.130 --> 01:15:45.630
you may have the prayer offered

01:15:45.630 --> 01:15:47.430
from your own location.

01:15:47.430 --> 01:15:50.430
Again, that song number 79.
